<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - PINION POSITION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="5">
        <title>PINION POSITION</title>
        <para>Ring gears and pinions are supplied in matched sets only. Matching numbers on both the pinion and ring
            gears are etched for verification. If a new gear set is being used, verify the numbers of each pinion and
            ring gear before proceeding with assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0200935">Figure 35</hotlnk>). Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s02009_9.xml" xrefid="f0200903">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0200935" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0200935" filename="../figg02/G0200935.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Ring Gear and Pinion</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Be sure mounting surfaces are free of burrs and dirt prior to assembly as they will affect pinion
                    position.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Make sure differential side bearing bores are clean and free of nicks.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove any burrs and wipe clean differential bearing bore IDs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200936">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200936" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200936" filename="../figg02/G0200936.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Clean Differential Bearing Bore IDs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pinion shims are available in the following thicknesses:</para>
            <table id="t0200902">
                <title>Pinion Shim Thickness</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="sqcolumn1" colwidth="1in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="sqcolumn2" colwidth="1in" colsep="1"/>
                    <thead valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>In.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>mm</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.005</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.127</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.010</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.254</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.030</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.762</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position shims on carrier housing so oil return holes align properly. Apply Loctite #609, or
                its equivalent, to all shim surfaces (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200937">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200937" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200937" filename="../figg02/G0200937.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Loctite on Shim Surfaces</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Be certain mounting surfaces and shims are free of dirt and nicks, or leaks may occur and
                        pinion position can be affected.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pinion and pinion cage assembly into carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200938">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200938" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200938" filename="../figg02/G0200938.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Install Pinion and Pinion Cage</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Studs can be used to assist in alignment.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten pinion cage to carrier bolts to 115 - 125 ft-lbs. (156 - 169 Nm). Bolts must be
                cleaned and coated with Loctite #271, or its equivalent (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200939">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200939" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200939" filename="../figg02/G0200939.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Tighten Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
